President Obama expresses his deep sadness upon hearing about the passing of David Broder, a renowned journalist. Broder began his career in Washington, DC and went on to become a highly respected political commentator, winning a Pulitzer Prize for his coverage of Watergate. He was affectionately known as the Dean of the Washington press corps. Despite his success, Broder remained kind and gracious, and he will be greatly missed. The President sends his thoughts and prayers to Broder's family and friends during this challenging time.